        <abstract> 
<p>Admires FJW’s article ["The boundaries of science", <hi rend="italic">Macmillan’s Mag.</hi> 4 (1861): 237–47]. Thinks she understands his book [<hi rend="italic">Origin</hi>] perfectly.</p> 
            <p>On design in nature: the more CD thinks on the subject the less he can see proof of it.</p>
        </abstract>
